Package it.polimi.ingsw.am16.common.tcpMessages.response

Class PlayCardResponse

java.lang.Object
it.polimi.ingsw.am16.common.tcpMessages.Payload
it.polimi.ingsw.am16.common.tcpMessages.response.PlayCardResponse
public class PlayCardResponse extends Payload
Message sent by the server to inform the client that a player has played a card. This payload also contains the information required by the client to update the view.

  • Constructor Details

    • PlayCardResponse

      public PlayCardResponse(String username, BoardCard card, SideType side, Position pos, Set<Position> addedLegalPositions, Set<Position> removedLegalPositions, Map<ResourceType,Integer> resourceCounts, Map<ObjectType,Integer> objectCounts)
      Parameters:
      username - The username of the player who played the card.
      card - The card that was played.
      side - The side on which the card was played.
      pos - The position where the card was played on the player's field.
      addedLegalPositions - The set of new positions where a card can now be played.
      removedLegalPositions - The set of positions where it is no longer possible to play a card.
      resourceCounts - The amount of each resource that the player has currently visible on their field.
      objectCounts - The amount of each object that the player has currently visible on their field.
